## 6. Potential Challenges and Mitigations

| Challenge | Mitigation |
|---|---|
| Futura is a commercial font; cannot be freely distributed | Ship with fallback stack (`Century Gothic`, `Trebuchet MS`). Include a README note about licensing. If Futura is available on the system, CSS will use it via `font-family`. |
| Apple Pay requires HTTPS and domain verification | Document this in README. For local dev, Apple Pay simply does not appear (Stripe handles this gracefully). The mock UI always shows the Apple Pay button for visual completeness. |
| `next-sanity`'s `NextStudio` may conflict with the blog layout | Use a route group `(blog)` for content pages and keep `/studio` outside it. The Studio page has no shared layout with blog pages. |
| ThirdWeb SDK requires a valid client ID for any wallet connection | The `MockThirdWebAuth` component provides a visual substitute. The real `ConnectButton` only mounts when `NEXT_PUBLIC_THIRDWEB_CLIENT_ID` is present. |
| Stripe `PaymentIntent` creation fails without `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` | The API route returns 503. The `StripeProvider` detects missing config and renders children without `<Elements>`, which triggers the mock UI. |

